This place serves some good food it is a buffet so you know what to expect. They try their best to clean up after people who are messy where food has dropped on the galley. But it's kind of hard because people are continuously moving back and forth over the food. They have a rule where you cannot talk on your cell phone while you are serving your own plate which is a good rule to put into effect. However although we're trying to keep sanitary conditions you don't want your customers to speak on their phones while serving their plates but you'll have your staff members Supply more foods to the tray in the hot plate or hot stand without a net covering their head. Or they will place food into the dishes without a plastic glove holding the utensil while they place the food inside of the pans at the hot Buffet. I don't understand it so which one carries the most germs if this is what we're looking to make sure we have less of the person who's talking on the phone or the worker who's not covering his or her hair and hands? Customer service here with the cashiers is always great always a smile. The location is easy to get to by train or car. They seem to always fit these fix-u-plate in the area where the majority of the people on Caribbeans. Now a lot of food served here or from the Caribbean background but that does not mean that it would not be just as successful in the neighborhood that is less Caribbeans. After all who doesn't know about jerk chicken, escovitch fish, peas and rice, by me if you been to Jamaica as a person who's not from the Caribbean or the Bahamas or Trinidad or Grenada or Barbados or if you have a nanny who is from one of these islands you know all about this Cuisine so why not Branch out into another neighborhood let everyone else taste the good cooking that fix u plate is known for.
